Last year, the October sales held in Paris to coincide with Art Basel=E2=80=
=99s Paris Plus art fair were an unexpected success. Sotheby=E2=80=99s was =
able to post strong numbers for works by Ren=C3=A9 Magritte, Lucio Fontana,=
 Pierre Soulages, and Frantisek Kupka in their Modern sale, while the singl=
e-owner Pauline Karpidas sale of the contents of her Hydra home produced a =
rousing =E2=82=AC35.5 million. Christie=E2=80=99s also did quite well: It s=
old Francois-Xavier Lalanne=E2=80=99s Rhinocretaire I for =E2=82=AC18.3 mil=
lion, a record price for the artist. The auction house also sold works from=
 the collection of Anne and Wolfgang Titze for =E2=82=AC27.7 million, and t=
he La Colombe d=E2=80=99Or hotel=E2=80=99s Joan Mir=C3=B3 for =E2=82=AC20.7=
 million.

This year, the auction houses have already begun announcing lots for the Pa=
ris sales, even
though they remain a full quarter away. Of course, some of the emphasis on =
Paris is a reflection of the quirks of the calendar. It=E2=80=99s July and =
the Contemporary market is still contracting, which means the midseason sal=
es in New York will not have publicity-worthy lots. And despite the fact th=
at Christie=E2=80=99s and Sotheby=E2=80=99s will, for the first time, be ho=
lding their Hong Kong sales in close proximity to each other in late Septem=
ber, the Asian market is in hibernation. But with the marketing upgrade of =
Paris+ (no, it=E2=80=99s not a streaming service) to Art Basel Paris and th=
e tailwind of attention many expect after the Olympics, along with the cons=
istent push from the Arnault and Pinault clans to draw attention to the cit=
y as the capital of the art-luxury industrial complex, there=E2=80=99s a da=
wning recognition that Paris will be playing a bigger role in the art trade=
=E2=80=94and its late October pit stop on the international swirl will beco=
me a signature annual event.

Sotheby=E2=80=99s, of course, has announced that its new, much larger, Pari=
s headquarters will open in October, which will bring it physically closer =
to its rivals. Just 270 meters from Christie=E2=80=99s and Gagosian, on one=
